The Digital Archive allows to upload, edit and remove documents and their metadata, if the user has the necessary permissions. There are several ways to manage the documents in the Digital Archive:

- **Workflow tasks (**[**Batch**](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Archive+Documents+%28DA%29+Batch+Workflow+Task+Reference)** and **[**On-Demand**](/doxee-platform/docs/archive-documents-da-on-demand-workflow-task-reference)**)**

- [**Digital Archiving API**](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Doxee+Platform+3+Digital+Archiving+API+Integration)

- **Action buttons in the Digital Archiving Portal**

This page explores how various actions can be performed on documents from within the user interface of the Digital Archiving Portal. For information on how to perform the same actions through workflow tasks or API, please see the relevant documentation.

## Upload documents
If you want to upload a new document to the Digital Archive, follow these steps:

- **Navigate to the Digital Archiving Portal** and open the Digital Archiving Store to which you want to upload the document.

- Click **Upload document** in the toolbar.

- In the pop-up window, **select the document category**, **enter the document metadata** and **upload the file** which you want to archive.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Upload** to complete the action.

> System indexes and custom indexes

When manually uploading a document to the Digital Archive, all system indexes which have been configured for the selected Digital Archiving Store resource will be populated automatically by the system. Any configured custom indexes are optional and can be filled manually in the upload pop-up window.

The system index **Document title** is always mandatory. If the Digital Archiving Store doesnt have a configured system index of this type, the system will use the filename of the uploaded file to fill this field.

## Update files and metadata
If you want to update an archived document or its metadata, follow these steps:

- **Navigate to the Digital Archiving Portal** and open the Digital Archiving Store which contains the document.

- **Select the document** which you want to update by marking its checkbox.

- Click **Edit metadata** in the toolbar.

- In the pop-up window, **enter the document metadata** which you want to update.

![Editing document metadata fields including invoice date, fiscal code, and invoice number.](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Edit **to complete the action.

> Editable indexes

Its only possible to edit custom indexes and the mandatory system index **Document title**. To make them editable, its necessary to enable editability for these indexes in the Digital Archiving Store resource under **Document properties**.

## Delete documents
If you want to delete a document from the Digital Archive, follow these steps:

- **Navigate to the Digital Archiving Portal** and open the Digital Archiving Store which contains the document.

- **Select one or more documents** which you want to delete by marking their checkboxes.

- Click **Delete documents** in the toolbar.

- **Confirm the action** in the pop-up window.

![Confirmation prompt for deleting one document, with options to confirm or cancel action.](data:image/png;base64,)
